The paper focuses on the study of indirect social ties and their usefulness for distributed applications, which falls under the scope of social networks and their analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of data-driven experiments and the quantification of social strength, which suggests the involvement of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper addresses the problems in friend-to-friend storage systems, which relates to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
